metadata:
  section_id: 49
  hadith_first: 8205
  hadith_last: 8265

hadiths[61]{hadithnumber,text,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro}:
8205,"The Messenger of Allah ﷺ said, ""Indeed, Allah has not sent down any disease except that He has also sent down its cure. The one who knows it, knows it, and the one who is ignorant of it, is ignorant of it.""",,,
8206,"I witnessed the Messenger of Allah ﷺ  and the Bedouins asking him, saying, ""O Messenger of Allah, do we have any hardship in such a matter? Do we have any hardship in such a matter?"" concerning things that are not harmful. He ﷺ  said, ""O slaves of Allah, Allah has relieved us of the hardship, except for the one who wrongs a Muslim's honor. That is the one who has hardship and perishes."" So they said, ""Should we seek medical treatment, O Messenger of Allah?"" He ﷺ  said, ""Yes, seek medical treatment, O slaves of Allah, for Allah Almighty has not created a disease except that He has also created its cure except for one disease."" They said, ""O Messenger of Allah, what is it?"" He ﷺ  said, ""Old age."" They said, ""O Messenger of Allah, what is the best thing that a person can be given?"" He ﷺ  said, ""Good manners.""",,,
8207,"About Ziyad ibn 'Ilaqah, among them is 'Amr ibn Qays al-Mulayy.",,,
8208,"Abu Bakr and Uthman, the sons of Abi Shayba, narrated: Jarir reported from Al-A'mash, and among them is Shu'ba ibn Al-Hajjaj.",,,
8209,"About Ziyad ibn 'Ilaqah, including Muhammad ibn Juhadah Al-Iyadi.",,,
8210,"Muhammad ibn Juhadah and among them is Abu Hamzah, Muhammad ibn Maymun Al-Sukkari narrated.",,,
8211,"Abu Al-Mujjah narrated that Abdan reported that Abu Hamza narrated from Ziyad bin 'Ilaqah, and among them is Abu Awana Al-Wadhdhah.",,,
8212,"""From Ziyad bin 'Ilaqah, and among them was Sufyan bin 'Uyaynah Al-Hilali.""",,,
8213,"From Ziyad ibn Ilaqah, and among them was Uthman ibn Hakim al-Awdi.",,,
8214,"We were sitting with the Prophet ﷺ  as if birds were perched on our heads. No one among us would speak until a man from the Bedouins came to him and said, ""O Messenger of Allah, give us your advice. Give us your advice."" He replied, ""O people of the Bedouins, Allah has made hardship unnecessary except for those who borrow from their brothers with the condition of repaying it. That is the hardship that destroys people."" They said, ""Should we seek treatment, O Messenger of Allah?"" He replied, ""Yes, indeed. Allah, the Mighty and Sublime, has not sent any disease except that He has also sent its cure, except for one disease."" They said, ""And what is that, O Messenger of Allah?"" He replied, ""Old age."" They asked, ""Who are the best of Allah's servants?"" He said, ""Those with the best manners among them."" Among them were Shu'ban bin Abdur-Rahman, Ziyad bin 'Ilaqah, and Zuhair bin Mu'awiyah Al-Ju'fi.",,,
8215,"From Usama bin Sharik, and among them is Amr bin Abi Qais al-Razi.",,,
8216,Abu Asim narrated.,,,
8217,From Ziyad bin Ilaqah and among them is Israel bin Yunus As-Sabi'iyyu.,,,
8218,null,,,
8219,"There is a remedy for every malady, and when the remedy is applied to the disease it is cured with the permission of Allah, the Exalted and Glorious. (Using translation from Muslim 2204)",,,
8220,"The Prophet ﷺ  said, ""Indeed, Allah has not sent down a disease or created a disease except that He has also sent down or created a cure for it. He has made it known to those who know it and unknown to those who do not know it, except for death."" They said, ""O Messenger of Allah, what is death?"" He said, ""It is 'as-sam'""",,,
8221,"A man came to the Messenger of Allah ﷺ and said, ""O Messenger of Allah, my brother complains of a stomach ache."" The Messenger of Allah ﷺ said, ""Give him honey to drink."" The man said, ""I have already given him to drink, but it only made him pass stool."" The Messenger of Allah ﷺ said, ""Allah has spoken the truth and the stomach of your brother has lied."" So, the man went and gave him honey to drink and he was cured.",,,
8222,"Narrated by the Prophet ﷺ , he said, ""Prophet Solomon ﷺ  used to see a plant growing in front of him when he stood in prayer, and he would ask it, 'What is your name?' And it would reply, 'Such and such.' Then he would ask it, 'What are you for?' And it would reply, 'For this and that,' whether it was for medicine or for planting. One day, while in prayer, he saw a plant growing in front of him and asked it, 'What is your name?' It replied, 'Al-Kharoob.' He asked it, 'What are you for?' It replied, 'For the destruction of this house.' Prophet Solomon ﷺ  said, 'O Allah! Let the jinn die until humans realize that the jinn do not know the unseen.' Then he carved it into a staff and leaned on it. Eventually, the earth swallowed it, and he fell, dying. They found him dead, surrounded by the staff. Thus, humans realized that if the jinn knew the unseen, they would not have suffered such a miserable punishment. Ibn Abbas used to recite it this way, and the earth showed gratitude to the jinn by providing water wherever it was.""",,,
8223,"He said, ""O Messenger of Allah, we used to seek Ruqyah and use medicines to cure ourselves. Does it go against the decree of Allah?"" He replied, ""It is part of the decree of Allah."" Al-Dhahabi remained silent about this in his summary.",,,
8224,"The Messenger of Allah ﷺ  said, ""You should consume cow's milk as it contains nutrients from every plant, and it is a remedy for every illness.""",,,
8225,“You should take the two that bring healing: Honey and the Qur’an.” (Using translation from Ibn Mājah 3452),,,
8226,"The Messenger of Allah ﷺ  said, ""When one of you is afflicted with a fever, let him pour cold water over himself for three nights.""",,,
8227,"About his mother, the wife of Zubair.",,,
8228,"Fever is from the vehement raging of the fire of Hell, so extinguish it with water. (Using translation from Muslim 2209c)",,,
8229,"The Prophet ﷺ  said, ""Indeed, fever is a portion of fire, so cool it down with water."" Authenticated.",,,
8230,"The Messenger of Allah ﷺ  said, ""Upon you is the black seed, drink it for it is a tree from the trees of Paradise. Its taste is bitter, but it is a cure for every disease."" Ahmed and others said that the liar is a sword.",,,
8231,"I returned to the Messenger of Allah ﷺ  and found a water pitcher hanging, and its water was dripping on him due to the intensity of the fever he was experiencing. So I said, ""O Messenger of Allah, if you invoke Allah to remove it from you?"" He replied, ""Verily, the prophets face the most severe trials, and then those who are closest to them."" Al-Dhahabi remained silent about it in the summary.",,,
8232,"From the Prophet ﷺ, he said, ""You should consume cow's milk, its fat, and avoid its meat, for its milk and fat are a remedy and healing, but its meat is a disease.""",,,
8233,"Shubrum He said: ""It is hot and too strong."" She said:""Then I used Senna as a laxative."" So the Prophet ﷺ said: ""If there was anything that would have a cure for death in it, then it would have been Senna."" (Using translation from Tirmidhī 2081)",,,
8234,I heard Zaid bin Arqam say: 'The Messenger of Allah ﷺ ordered us to use Qust Al-Bahri and oil to treat Pleurisy.' (Using translation from Tirmidhī 2079),,,
8235,"The translation of the given sentence is as follows:  ""When they said, 'We are afraid of the man who is lying on the side of the Messenger of Allah,' the Prohpet said, 'Indeed, it is from Satan, and Allah would not make him have power over me.'""",,,
8236,The Messenger of Allah ﷺ died from pleurisy',,,
8237,"The Prophet Muhammad ﷺ  said, ""The pain in the side is the result of the movement of the kidney's vein. If it is agitated, treat it with boiled water and honey.""",,,
8238,It was narrated from ʿAli ؓ that The Messenger of Allah ﷺ was treated with cupping and he gave the cupper his fee. (Using translation from Aḥmad 1129),,,
8239,"A woman came to the messenger of Allah ﷺ and said, ""O messenger of Allah, my son has an illness."" He said, ""Do not burn the throats of your children (by forcing them) but treat them with Indian costus and lotus leaves."" Hammad and Yahya are weak narrators.",,,
8240,"I heard the Prophet of Allah ﷺ  describing oil and arrowroot as being part of the same side. Qatadah said, ""They are born from the side that complains of it.""",,,
8241,"The Prophet ﷺ  entered upon Aisha, and with her was a woman who had a child whose nose was bleeding. The Prophet ﷺ  said, ""What is the matter with him?"" They replied, ""It is due to Udhrah."" He said, ""Do not kill your children because of Udhrah. Whenever any of you is afflicted with such a thing, let her take a Hindy (Indian) Qasah, grind it, then let her put some of its powder in the water and let her lick it with her saliva and administer it to the child."" Then the Prophet ﷺ  ordered Aisha to do it and she did it for the child, and he was cured.",,,
8242,"I heard the Messenger of Allah ﷺ  while I was his companion, saying, ""The tree and the dates are from Paradise.""",,,
8243,"""When we arrived at the Prophet Muhammad ﷺ, they brought him dates from their harvest and they started eating them. They named those dates after themselves and said, 'O Messenger of Allah, we do not know the names of these dates except for the ones we named after ourselves.' Then the Prophet ﷺ told a man from the close companions to feed us from the remaining dates. The Prophet ﷺ said, 'These are the Barnee dates, and they are the best among your dates, and they are a medicine without any illness.' Al-Dhahabi remained silent about it in his summary.""",,,
8244,"The Messenger of Allah ﷺ  came to me along with Ali, and he was riding a she-camel. I said to him, ""We have some dates hanging up."" The Messenger of Allah ﷺ  got up and ate, and then Ali got up and ate. The Prophet ﷺ  said, ""Slow down, Ali, for you are a she-camel."" So Ali sat down and then I prepared for them some roasted meat and barley. The Prophet ﷺ  said, ""Now, Ali, you will improve from this.""",,,
8245,"From the Prophet ﷺ, he said: ""Upon you is to use al-talbineh, the beneficial plant. By the One in Whose hand is the soul of Muhammad, it surely washes the inside of one of you as water washes the dirt off the face."" She said: ""And when anyone among his family complained, the barmah (a type of medicine) would continuously be put on the fire until one of his limbs was affected, either death or life.""",,,
8246,"the maid-servant of the Messenger of Allah ﷺ, said: No one complained to the Messenger of Allah ﷺ of a headache but he told him to get himself cupped, or of a pain in his legs but he told him to dye them with henna. (Using translation from Abū Dāʾūd 3858)",,,
8247,"""The Prophet ﷺ described for them in the veins of women that they should take a vein similar to that of a sheep, not too big nor too small, then it should be cut into three parts and every day they should drink a part.""",,,
8248,"“The Messenger of Allah ﷺ said: ‘You should use antimony, for it improves the eyesight and makes the hair (eyelashes) grow.’” (Using translation from Ibn Mājah 3495)",,,
8249,"""The Messenger of Allah ﷺ  used to apply kohl three times with antimony before going to sleep every night.""",,,
8250,"A boil appeared on my neck, and it was mentioned to the Prophet ﷺ, so he said, ""Open it and do not let it eat the flesh or suck the blood.""",,,
8251,"""I fell ill, so my family took care of everything for me, even the water. I became thirsty one night and there was no one around. I approached a hanging water container and took a sip from it. I stood up feeling healthy again. I wanted to see the effect of that drink on my body."" Aisha used to say, ""Don't attribute anything to the sick person.""",,,
8252,"I will not go away unless you get yourself cupped, for I heard Messenger of Allah ﷺ say: It is a remedy. (Using translation from Muslim 2205a)",,,
8253,"The Prophet ﷺ  said, ""Whenever I passed by a gathering of angels, they would always instruct me to get cupping therapy.""",,,
8254,"""The Prophet ﷺ  used to perform I'tikaf during the seventeenth, eighteen, and twenty-first nights.""",,,
8255,"I heard the Messenger of Allah ﷺ  saying, ""Cupping on an empty stomach is the most beneficial. It brings blessings and healing, increases intelligence, and improves memory. Get cupped on Thursday for the blessings of Allah Almighty, and avoid cupping on Friday, Saturday, and Sunday. Get cupped on Monday and Tuesday, as it is the day when Allah cured Job from his afflictions. There will be no contagious disease or leprosy except on Wednesday and Wednesday night. Indeed, Job was afflicted on Wednesday."" All the narrators of this hadith are trustworthy except for Usman ibn Ja'far, as I don't know about his reliability or integrity.",,,
8256,"The Prophet Muhammad ﷺ said, ""Whoever performs Hijama (cupping) on Wednesday or Saturday and then sees blood, he should not blame anyone but himself."" Suleiman ibn Arqam (a narrator) has abandoned this hadith.",,,
8257,"Abu Hind described the Prophet ﷺ as having a face filled with pain, and he said, ""If there is any good in the treatment that you seek, it is through cupping.""",,,
8258,"“The Messenger of Allah ﷺ said: ‘What a good slave is the cupper. He takes away the blood, reduces pressure on the spine, and improves the eyesight.’” (Using translation from Ibn Mājah 3478)",,,
8259,“Do not force your sick ones to eat or drink. Allah will feed them and give them to drink.” (Using translation from Ibn Mājah 3444),,,
8260,The Messenger of Allah ﷺ prohibited unclean medicine. (Using translation from Abū Dāʾūd 3870),,,
8261,"""A doctor mentioned the medicine in front of the Messenger of Allah ﷺ , then he mentioned that the frog is included in the medicine, so the Prophet ﷺ  forbade killing it.""",,,
8262,"The Prophet Muhammad ﷺ  said, ""Every person has a vein in their head that is affected by leprosy, and when it becomes active, Allah sends them a cold, so do not treat it."" It appears to be a subject.",,,
8263,“I came to the Prophet ﷺ and in front of him there were some bread and dates. The Prophet ﷺ said: ‘Come and eat.’ So I started to eat some of the dates. Then the Prophet ﷺ said: ‘Are you eating dates when you have an inflammation in your eye?’ I said: ‘I am chewing from the other side.’ And the Messenger of Allah ﷺ smiled.” (Using translation from Ibn Mājah 3443),,,
8264,"The Messenger of Allah ﷺ  said, ""Beware of sitting in the sun, as it fades the clothing, weakens the wind, and reveals hidden diseases."" That is from the wisdom of the miller.",,,
8265,"I entered upon the Messenger of Allah ﷺ  and in his hand was a small bag. He threw it towards me and said, ""Keep it, O Abu Muhammad, as it soothes the heart."" Al-Dhahabi remained silent about it in his summary.",,,
